Patty Pravo (born Nicoletta Strambelli, 9 April 1948 Venice, Italy) is an Italian pop singer whose career has spanned more than four decades. Her first single "Pazza idea" ("Crazy Idea"), released in 1973, was the first pop song aired on Vatican Radio.
